<TABLEFOOTNOTE LBL="a" ID="ch15.3DmanipTF4a">See &ldquo;Phases of 3D Manipulation.&rdquo;</TABLEFOOTNOTE>
<TABLEFOOTNOTE LBL="b" ID="ch15.3DmanipTF4b">See &ldquo;3D Manipulation Feedback.&rdquo;</TABLEFOOTNOTE>
</TABLE>
<PARAGRAPH><FIGURE>&space;<GRAPHIC FILE="fig.15-6.gif" POSITION="INLINE" SCALE="FALSE"><CAPTION LBL="15-6"><PREFIX>Figure 15-6 </PREFIX><XREFTARGET ID="80094">Constrained Rotation Sequence</CAPTION>
</FIGURE>
</PARAGRAPH>
<PARAGRAPH><XREF IDREF="80094" TYPE="GRAPHIC">Figure&nbsp;15-6</XREF> shows the sequence of events for constrained rotation. When the user grabs a rotation handle, the rotation feedback appears indicating that the user must choose one of two axes for the rotation. The user chooses a direction and an axis for rotation by dragging along one of the two arrows. Once the axis has been chosen, all user input is interpreted to rotate the object around the selected axis in the given direction.</PARAGRAPH>
</SECTION2>
<SECTION2 LBL="" HELPID = ""><TITLE><XREFTARGET ID="26561">Free 3D Rotation</TITLE><PARAGRAPH>In free rotation, the object rotates around a point rather than an axis; that is, the object can rotate around all three axes simultaneously. Typically, the default center of rotation is at the center of the object's bounding box. The user presses the &lt;Shift> modifier key to indicate free rotation. <INDEXTARGET ID="ch15.3Dmanip40"><!-- POSTPROCESSDATA: ch15.3Dmanip40|&lt;Shift\> key:free rotation free rotation rotation:free --></PARAGRAPH>
<PARAGRAPH>Free rotation is similar to constrained rotation (see <XREF IDREF="48709" TYPE="TABLE">Table&nbsp;15-5</XREF>). However, as shown in <XREF IDREF="41574" TYPE="TABLE">Table&nbsp;15-6</XREF>, the grab phase displays a virtual trackball as the rotation feedback, and the drag phase rotates the object around the center of rotation. </PARAGRAPH>
<TABLE COLUMNS="3"><CAPTION LBL="15-6"><PREFIX>Table 15-6 </PREFIX><XREFTARGET ID="41574">  <EMPHASIS>(continued)        </EMPHASIS>Phases of Free Rotation<INDEXTARGET ID="ch15.3Dmanip41"><!-- POSTPROCESSDATA: ch15.3Dmanip41|free rotation:phases phases:free rotation --></CAPTION>
<TABLEHEADING><CELL LEFT="0" WIDTH="49"><PARAGRAPH>Phase</PARAGRAPH>
</CELL>
<CELL LEFT="55" WIDTH="139"><PARAGRAPH>User Action</PARAGRAPH>
</CELL>
<CELL LEFT="200" WIDTH="198"><PARAGRAPH>Application Response</PARAGRAPH>
</CELL>
</TABLEHEADING>
<TABLEBODY><ROW><CELL LEFT="0" WIDTH="49"><PARAGRAPH>Approach<INDEXTARGET ID="ch15.3Dmanip42"><!-- POSTPROCESSDATA: ch15.3Dmanip42|approach phase:rotation --></PARAGRAPH>
</CELL>
<CELL LEFT="55" WIDTH="139"><PARAGRAPH>Same as for constrained rotation 
(see <XREF IDREF="48709" TYPE="TABLE">Table&nbsp;15-5</XREF>).</PARAGRAPH>
</CELL>
<CELL LEFT="200" WIDTH="198"><PARAGRAPH>Same as for constrained rotation. </PARAGRAPH>
</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW><CELL LEFT="0" WIDTH="49"><PARAGRAPH>Grab<INDEXTARGET ID="ch15.3Dmanip43"><!-- POSTPROCESSDATA: ch15.3Dmanip43|grab phase:free rotation --></PARAGRAPH>
</CELL>
<CELL LEFT="55" WIDTH="139"><PARAGRAPH>User presses and holds &lt;Shift> 
key and left mouse button while 
pointer is over rotation handle of 
interest.</PARAGRAPH>
</CELL>
<CELL LEFT="200" WIDTH="198"><PARAGRAPH>Same as for constrained rotation with this 
exception: Rotation feedback consists of three 
rings representing a virtual trackball (see 
<XREF IDREF="87889" TYPE="GRAPHIC">Figure&nbsp;15-7</XREF>). This feedback is displayed in guide 
style. No choice arrows are provided.</PARAGRAPH>
</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW><CELL LEFT="0" WIDTH="49"><PARAGRAPH>Drag<INDEXTARGET ID="ch15.3Dmanip44"><!-- POSTPROCESSDATA: ch15.3Dmanip44|drag phase: free rotation --></PARAGRAPH>
